DESCRIPTION:Looking for something to do after school? Come out to our Afte
 r School Club and learn new things\, make stuff\, meet other kids and have
  fun! For ages\n6-12.\nDrop-in.\nUpcoming Programs:\nMarch 31 - Easter Bun
 ny Masks\nSnacks are offered during the After School Club for participants
 .\nFood may contain or have come into contact with common allergens. Ingre
 dient lists will be available. Snacks are generously supported\, in part\,
  by donors.\nIf you or your child lives with a disability\, and requires a
 n accessibility accommodation to participate in this program\, please cont
 act Accessibility Services by email\, accessibleservices@tpl.ca\, or voice
 mail\, 416-393-7099\, to make a request. Please contact us at least three 
 weeks in advance.
LOCATION:Jones
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696abaf8b0595799c096d1fd
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
