UID:69b1e5a4491b809c6f1fbe2c@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn the very basics of Blender and how you can optimize your
  3D computer graphics model for 3D printing at the Toronto Public Library
 ’s Digital Innovation Hubs. This class includes hands-on instruction wit
 h Blender to create your 3D object file for printing on a Prusa MK3S+ 3D p
 rinter.\nBasic computer knowledge and experience are required.\nRegistrati
 on is required for this class and begins March 19th\, 2026 at 12:30pm.\nPl
 ease bring your own USB key if you would like to keep your file.\nNote: Yo
 ur spot will not be guaranteed after 5 minutes of the start of the program
 .\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form i
 s collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\,
  sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for
  event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about
  how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline st
 aff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON
  M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, 2nd Floor - eLearning Lab
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b1e5a4491b809c6f1fbe2c
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
