DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T173000
UID:69bd9ca007a74a47597a2645@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop\, Coach Joshua "Scribe" Watkis will utilize R
 hythm and Poetry (Rap) as an accessible and engaging entry point for young
  propel to connect with the spoken and written word.\nParticipants will le
 arn the short history and mechanics of Rap\, discuss its personal relevanc
 e\, practice basic rhyme schemes and literary devices\, and ultimately wri
 te and share their own 8-16 bar verse.
