BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:3D Design with Onshape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T160000
UID:69b619a081b67dfe32acab73@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to create parametric designs using cloud based softw
 are Onshape.\nThis hands-on workshop introduces participants to the fundam
 entals of 3D design using Onshape\, a cloud-based CAD software. Whether yo
 u're an aspiring engineer\, designer\, or hobbyist\, this session provides
  the tools and knowledge to start creating your own 3D models.\nWhat You
 ’ll Learn:\nGetting Started:\nOverview of Onshape's interface\, navigati
 on tools\, and cloud-based collaboration features.\nCore Design Principles
 :\nUnderstanding 3D modeling basics\, including sketches\, extrusions\, an
 d revolutions.\nHands-On Practice:\nCreating simple 3D parts\, assembling 
 components\, and exploring design modifications.\nBest Practices:\nTips fo
 r efficient modeling\, managing design iterations\, and exporting models f
 or 3D printing or other applications.\nThis program is ideal for beginners
  with no prior experience in CAD software\, as well as those looking to ex
 plore Onshape's capabilities.\nRegistration will start 2 weeks before this
  class. Computers will be provided.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe p
 ersonal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Librar
 y under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The
  information will only be used for event and program registration\, delive
 ry and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your informatio
 n can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-59
 81\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Danforth/Coxwell\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b619a081b67dfe32acab73
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
